
*/
===========================================================
===========================================================
Whats the porpuse of this script? 
Create Database and Schemas

Script Purpose:
This script creates a new database named 'DataWarehouse' and sets up the initial schema structure.
It creates three schemas used in the data warehouse architecture: 'bronze', 'silver', and 'gold'.

This script is intended for the initial setup of the data warehouse environment.

*/ 
  


USE master;
GO
-- Drop and recreate the 'DataWarehouse' database
IF EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM sys.databases WHERE name = 'Datakarehouse")
BEGIN
ALTER DATABASE DataWarehouse SET SINGLE_USER WITH ROLLBACK INMEDIATE;
DROP DATABASE DataWarehouse;
END;
GO
-- Create the DataWarehouse' database
CREATE
DATABASE Datawarehouse;
GO
USE DataWarehouse:
GO
- Create Schemas
CREATE SCHEMA bronze;
GO
CREATE SCHEMA silver;
GO
